    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/dr-cou1-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. Validation results demonstrate NIH prediction accuracy within quantified uncertainty bounds at 4 of 5 operating points; the outlier at the highest flow-speed combination is within the transitional flow regime and is acknowledged in the model form assessment. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied across all nominal CPB operating points. The credibility evidence package supports regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device tolerance analysis.",
